---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Refund & Cancellation Policy — PlayShip"
  description="When PlayShip refunds, when it doesn't, and how to cancel a submission engagement."
>
  <main class="container legal">
    <p class="eyebrow mono">REFUND & CANCELLATION</p>
    <h1>Refund &amp; Cancellation Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated mono">Last updated: 24 May 2026</p>

    <p>
      PlayShip sells a delivered professional service. The rules below describe
      when you can cancel and when a refund is due.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Cancellation by you</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Before work starts:</strong> 100% refund, less any non-recoverable payment processor fees, if you cancel before we have begun work (typically within 24 hours of payment).</li>
      <li><strong>After work has started but before submission:</strong> 50% refund. The remainder covers time already spent on audit, listing copy, asset preparation, and Play Console configuration.</li>
      <li><strong>After the build has been submitted to Google Play:</strong> no refund, because the service has been performed.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Express tier guarantee</h2>
    <p>
      The Express tier carries a "live in 7 days or full refund" guarantee. If
      your app is not in at least the Internal Testing track within 7 calendar
      days of us receiving a working AAB, signing key, and Play Console access,
      you are entitled to a full refund on request.
    </p>
    <p>
      The guarantee does not apply where the delay is caused by Google review
      times beyond our control, missing or invalid inputs from you, policy
      violations in the app itself that require code changes, or force majeure.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Cancellation by us</h2>
    <p>
      We may decline or stop work if the app violates Google Play policy,
      involves illegal content, infringes third-party rights, or if the client
      becomes uncontactable for more than 14 days. In that case we refund the
      portion of the fee for work not yet performed.
    </p>

    <h2>4. How to request a refund</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href="mailto:avinashsreekumar007@gmail.com">avinashsreekumar007@gmail.com</a>
      with your order reference and the reason for the request. Eligible
      refunds are issued to the original payment method within 5–10 business
      days of approval. Stripe and bank settlement times may add a few days.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Chargebacks</h2>
    <p>
      If you have a concern please contact us first. Initiating a chargeback
      without first allowing us a reasonable opportunity to resolve the issue
      may delay or void any refund.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Avinash Sreekumar · Trivandrum, Kerala, India ·
      <a href="mailto:avinashsreekumar007@gmail.com">avinashsreekumar007@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 760px;
    padding-block: 80px;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--approved);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  h1 {
    margin-top: 16px;
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  h2 {
    margin-top: 40px;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .updated {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 12px;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
  p, li {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  li {
    margin-block: 6px;
  }
  a {
    color: var(--ink);
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--line-strong);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--ink);
  }
</style>
